WEBVTT

00:00:08.025 --> 00:00:10.725
[♪♪]

00:00:26.343 --> 00:00:29.144
[GRUNTING]

00:00:59.943 --> 00:01:02.711
[SIGHS]

00:01:25.419 --> 00:01:27.820
Anastasia?

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:30.538
Stop.

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:38.880
Cuff yourself to the bedpost.

00:01:46.290 --> 00:01:47.639
Don't bother.

00:01:50.644 --> 00:01:52.661
[CHUCKLES]

00:02:00.737 --> 00:02:02.354
[GUN THUDS]

00:02:08.445 --> 00:02:12.447
You look good. Healthy.

00:02:13.767 --> 00:02:15.311
Pale, though.

00:02:15.335 --> 00:02:18.664
I think maybe you
live on the East Coast.

00:02:18.688 --> 00:02:23.836
For years I've been
thinking, "Where is she?

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:28.074
Is she close or
half the world away?

00:02:28.098 --> 00:02:31.444
Is she still nervous
when it thunders?

00:02:31.468 --> 00:02:36.366
Does she remember our
walks in Coney Island?

00:02:36.390 --> 00:02:39.774
Getting borscht from Alexa's?"

00:02:48.018 --> 00:02:51.303
They're all there,
every last one.

00:03:01.198 --> 00:03:03.659
And what do you want
in exchange for this?

00:03:03.683 --> 00:03:06.400
Just let me go.

00:03:08.422 --> 00:03:13.069
He found you
faster than I thought.

00:03:13.093 --> 00:03:15.722
He did in one week

00:03:15.746 --> 00:03:19.391
what I failed to do in 15 years.

00:03:19.415 --> 00:03:22.812
True love, huh? Ha, ha.

00:03:22.836 --> 00:03:25.414
Just take the diamonds
and consider me dead.

00:03:25.438 --> 00:03:27.417
Or what?

00:03:27.441 --> 00:03:30.492
You've only given
me half of what I want.

00:03:32.046 --> 00:03:34.991
I want him.

00:03:35.015 --> 00:03:37.927
I can't do that.

00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:41.002
If you could, you would be free.

00:03:48.963 --> 00:03:50.429
Your word?

00:03:51.715 --> 00:03:53.631
My word.

00:03:56.770 --> 00:04:01.417
Now, how are you
going to get away?

00:04:01.441 --> 00:04:03.558
There's something
else in the bag for you.

00:04:06.379 --> 00:04:09.408
[GASPS THEN CHUCKLES]

00:04:09.432 --> 00:04:13.285
[IN UKRAINIAN]

00:04:32.973 --> 00:04:34.818
[KISSES]

00:04:34.842 --> 00:04:36.341
Bye, Daddy.

00:04:42.816 --> 00:04:45.800
[♪♪]

00:06:01.878 --> 00:06:03.227
[HORN HONKING]

00:06:07.935 --> 00:06:09.384
[CHATTERING]

00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.699
MAN 1: Say "champ." Say
"champ." MAN 2: Champ!

00:06:13.723 --> 00:06:15.868
Banshee, PA! What's up, baby?

00:06:15.892 --> 00:06:17.721
What can you tell
us about this fight?

00:06:17.745 --> 00:06:20.022
What can I tell you about...?
I can tell you'd better...

00:06:20.046 --> 00:06:23.809
This fight will cement your
credibility with the commission.

00:06:23.833 --> 00:06:26.062
Give me another week,
and I'll have us cleared

00:06:26.086 --> 00:06:28.732
to break ground on the hotel.

00:06:28.756 --> 00:06:32.902
I must admit I had
my doubts, Kai,

00:06:32.926 --> 00:06:35.338
but you pulled it off.

00:06:35.362 --> 00:06:37.374
It's our casino. We're
putting up the purse.

00:06:37.398 --> 00:06:39.776
He was just the middleman.
BENJAMIN: Alex, enough.

00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:42.445
SANCHEZ: The champ is in the
building, ladies and gentlemen.

00:06:42.469 --> 00:06:44.047
The champ is in the building.

00:06:44.071 --> 00:06:46.082
Mr. Sanchez, Kai Proctor.

00:06:46.106 --> 00:06:48.067
Welcome to Banshee.
Glad to be here.

00:06:48.091 --> 00:06:50.953
This is Benjamin Longshadow.
His tribe runs the Kinaho Moon.

00:06:50.977 --> 00:06:53.072
Chief. It's an honor
to have you here.

00:06:53.096 --> 00:06:55.909
Alex Longshadow. Oh. Hey.

00:06:55.933 --> 00:06:58.044
Mr. Sanchez, if you
would do us the honor,

00:06:58.068 --> 00:07:00.296
a few shots with the
casino in the background.

00:07:00.320 --> 00:07:02.098
Man, of... Come
on, man, of course.

00:07:02.122 --> 00:07:04.066
MAN 4: Right this way.

00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:06.770
Mr. Proctor, Douglas
Dern, Damien's manager.

00:07:06.794 --> 00:07:09.088
We spoke on the phone.
We did. Pleasure to meet you.

00:07:09.112 --> 00:07:12.392
You said the place was
old. You didn't say ancient.

00:07:12.416 --> 00:07:15.978
The Kinaho feel a powerful
connection to their past.

00:07:16.002 --> 00:07:17.363
In the case of the Kinaho Moon,

00:07:17.387 --> 00:07:19.548
a little too powerful,
in my opinion.

00:07:19.572 --> 00:07:21.717
I would have preferred to
have the new casino built

00:07:21.741 --> 00:07:23.086
before we hosted Mr. Sanchez,

00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:26.789
but rest assured
the money is real.

00:07:26.813 --> 00:07:29.909
Yeah, it had better be.

00:07:29.933 --> 00:07:32.733
SANCHEZ: He's gonna
look worse soon, I promise.

00:07:35.171 --> 00:07:37.550
Nice casino. Not bad.

00:07:37.574 --> 00:07:39.319
[SLOT MACHINES DINGING]

00:07:39.343 --> 00:07:41.243
Not bad at all.

00:07:43.763 --> 00:07:45.764
[POWER TOOL WHIRRING]

00:07:49.436 --> 00:07:50.663
There it is, baby.

00:07:50.687 --> 00:07:52.165
That's where I do my thing.

00:07:52.189 --> 00:07:53.989
KAI: This way, Mr. Sanchez.

00:07:57.127 --> 00:07:59.811
You don't approve.

00:08:02.716 --> 00:08:06.011
The hotel. The revenue it will
earn should be for our people.

00:08:06.035 --> 00:08:07.980
We shouldn't be including
a man like Proctor.

00:08:08.004 --> 00:08:12.619
A man like that gets
things done quickly.

00:08:12.643 --> 00:08:14.354
We're building something

00:08:14.378 --> 00:08:17.378
that will sustain our
tribe for years to come.

00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:21.527
When I go to the spirits,

00:08:21.551 --> 00:08:24.519
I want to have seen
the start of it all.

00:08:34.548 --> 00:08:35.847
[GRUNTING]

00:08:37.533 --> 00:08:39.017
[SCREAMS]

00:09:05.178 --> 00:09:06.427
[SCREAMS]

00:09:16.506 --> 00:09:18.518
Are you sure you
wouldn't prefer a hotel?

00:09:18.542 --> 00:09:21.220
It's a quick call. I can have
you in the presidential suite.

00:09:21.244 --> 00:09:23.989
No, no, no. My trailer
goes wherever I go.

00:09:24.013 --> 00:09:26.358
I don't like to be too
pampered before a fight.

00:09:26.382 --> 00:09:28.278
Besides, there'll be
plenty of time for that

00:09:28.302 --> 00:09:30.162
after I put Hollister's
noose up there.

00:09:30.186 --> 00:09:32.419
As agreed.

00:09:34.457 --> 00:09:36.057
Thank you.

00:09:38.979 --> 00:09:40.590
I think I like this town.

00:09:40.614 --> 00:09:43.059
We also made some
improvements on your bedroom.

00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:45.750
<i>I think you'll be pleased.</i>

00:09:48.387 --> 00:09:53.302
WOMAN: <i>♪ Amazing Grace ♪</i>

00:09:53.326 --> 00:09:54.787
<i>♪ How sweet... ♪</i>

00:09:54.811 --> 00:09:57.545
Now I know I like this town.

00:09:58.815 --> 00:10:03.762
♪ That saved a wretch ♪

00:10:03.786 --> 00:10:08.634
♪ Like me ♪

00:10:08.658 --> 00:10:14.807
♪ I once was lost ♪

00:10:14.831 --> 00:10:19.444
♪ But now am found ♪

00:10:19.468 --> 00:10:23.132
♪ Was blind ♪

00:10:23.156 --> 00:10:30.640
♪ But now I see ♪

00:10:30.664 --> 00:10:35.333
♪ 'Twas Grace That taught... ♪

00:10:37.788 --> 00:10:40.616
You have the department's
deepest sympathies.

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:42.584
Mrs. Schumacher,
I'm so, so sorry.

00:10:42.608 --> 00:10:45.043
Sorry for your loss.

00:10:53.286 --> 00:10:54.566
Sorry, ma'am.

00:11:04.865 --> 00:11:06.308
GORDON: Sheriff Hood.

00:11:06.332 --> 00:11:07.565
Gordon.

00:11:09.302 --> 00:11:11.814
Hi, Deva.

00:11:11.838 --> 00:11:15.051
Pretty tough day for everyone.

00:11:15.075 --> 00:11:16.341
Yep.

00:11:20.363 --> 00:11:23.108
Say, why don't you join
us for dinner tonight?

00:11:23.132 --> 00:11:25.861
Nothing fancy. I'm just
gonna grill out some burgers.

00:11:25.885 --> 00:11:29.464
Oh, honey, you know...
LUCAS: That sounds great.

00:11:29.488 --> 00:11:31.189
Thanks, Gordon.

00:11:32.242 --> 00:11:33.685
Why don't we say about 6?

00:11:33.709 --> 00:11:35.121
Sure. See you there.

00:11:35.145 --> 00:11:37.178
Good.

00:11:43.820 --> 00:11:45.681
So how do you like
your burger, sheriff?

00:11:45.705 --> 00:11:47.939
Uh, medium rare, thanks.

00:11:50.426 --> 00:11:52.404
Can I see your gun? Yeah, sure.

00:11:52.428 --> 00:11:56.141
No. Thank you. You
don't need to see his gun.

00:11:56.165 --> 00:11:58.911
GORDON: Hon, why don't you,
uh, grab the sheriff another beer?

00:11:58.935 --> 00:12:01.380
I'll get it, Mom.

00:12:01.404 --> 00:12:03.924
LUCAS: Thanks. DEVA: Yeah.

00:12:09.612 --> 00:12:11.557
DEVA: Here you go. Thank you.

00:12:11.581 --> 00:12:14.141
DEVA: Yep.

00:12:15.769 --> 00:12:18.619
So, Deva, how are you doing?

00:12:20.223 --> 00:12:22.335
I don't know.

00:12:22.359 --> 00:12:25.371
I still can't believe it.

00:12:25.395 --> 00:12:27.528
It takes some time.

00:12:28.898 --> 00:12:30.376
[MAX COUGHING]

00:12:30.400 --> 00:12:33.968
Deva, would you go
get... Yeah. Hold on, Maxie.

00:12:38.074 --> 00:12:40.241
Nice and deep, bubba.

00:12:42.545 --> 00:12:44.273
DEVA: You okay?

00:12:44.297 --> 00:12:46.381
That's the way.

00:12:47.567 --> 00:12:49.334
DEVA: You good?

00:12:54.574 --> 00:12:56.585
What's wrong with
him? It's been happening

00:12:56.609 --> 00:12:57.992
since he was a toddler.

00:12:59.746 --> 00:13:02.658
LUCAS: Is he...? Is he okay?

00:13:02.682 --> 00:13:04.315
He has good days and bad days.

00:13:06.168 --> 00:13:07.635
Huh.

00:13:10.740 --> 00:13:13.802
Hey, Max, why don't you go ahead

00:13:13.826 --> 00:13:17.244
and touch the gun,
just for a second.

00:13:21.984 --> 00:13:23.300
Yeah. Ha, ha.

00:13:28.824 --> 00:13:31.303
GORDON: Sheriff, we never
got a chance to thank you

00:13:31.327 --> 00:13:33.856
for pulling Deva out of
that mess the other night.

00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:37.843
Ah. So how did the
arraignments go?

00:13:37.867 --> 00:13:41.130
Well, all the men you arrested
identified this guy Hanson,

00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:42.814
but apparently he's long gone.

00:13:42.838 --> 00:13:45.434
And either they don't
know or won't talk about

00:13:45.458 --> 00:13:47.336
where the skulls came from.

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:49.171
It's not that I can't guess.

00:13:49.195 --> 00:13:52.024
Whores, gambling, drugs.

00:13:52.048 --> 00:13:54.327
All crooked roads in
Banshee lead to one man,

00:13:54.351 --> 00:13:56.384
and that's Kai Proctor.

00:14:00.823 --> 00:14:02.935
I'll get us some
more drinks, eh?

00:14:02.959 --> 00:14:05.726
LUCAS: Great.

00:14:13.336 --> 00:14:14.847
Alone at last.

00:14:14.871 --> 00:14:17.305
Shut up.

00:14:19.558 --> 00:14:20.824
What happened?

00:14:25.064 --> 00:14:26.547
Heavy bag workout.

00:14:28.151 --> 00:14:33.087
Unh, not unless it
was a bag of bones.

00:14:38.995 --> 00:14:41.378
Ana...

00:14:43.249 --> 00:14:44.498
it's me.

00:14:45.918 --> 00:14:48.430
Mm, no, you're different.

00:14:48.454 --> 00:14:49.720
How?

00:14:52.074 --> 00:14:54.375
You used to be kind.

00:14:56.512 --> 00:14:57.911
[SCOFFS]

00:15:00.116 --> 00:15:01.748
You know,

00:15:02.852 --> 00:15:04.563
you get locked up,

00:15:04.587 --> 00:15:06.848
forgotten about for 15 years,

00:15:06.872 --> 00:15:08.251
see how kind
you feel after that.

00:15:08.275 --> 00:15:09.702
Now, I know you're angry, but...

00:15:09.726 --> 00:15:11.887
Angry?

00:15:11.911 --> 00:15:13.877
You have no fucking idea.

00:15:23.489 --> 00:15:24.934
GORDON: Hey,
where are you going?

00:15:24.958 --> 00:15:28.375
Uh, I got a call.
Thanks for the food.

00:15:43.075 --> 00:15:46.076
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

00:15:58.191 --> 00:16:01.609
Look, um, you
wanna talk about it?

00:16:10.353 --> 00:16:12.253
[CHUCKLES]

00:16:13.622 --> 00:16:14.938
Drinking alone?

00:16:22.832 --> 00:16:25.600
To keeping secrets.

00:16:35.612 --> 00:16:38.007
Hey, um...

00:16:38.031 --> 00:16:39.275
Rebecca.

00:16:39.299 --> 00:16:41.565
Rebecca.

00:16:43.502 --> 00:16:45.197
I think you should go home.

00:16:45.221 --> 00:16:47.221
[BOTH MOANING]

00:16:54.196 --> 00:16:55.496
No, you don't.

00:16:57.233 --> 00:16:59.612
[GRUNTING]

00:16:59.636 --> 00:17:03.298
What, are you saving
yourself for someone?

00:17:03.322 --> 00:17:05.356
[PANTING]

00:17:11.180 --> 00:17:12.624
Rebecca, we can't...

00:17:12.648 --> 00:17:14.682
Shut up.

00:17:27.113 --> 00:17:30.976
Look, you told me to call
if she came back again.

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:33.034
Well, she's back.

00:18:07.653 --> 00:18:10.766
Hi, Uncle Kai.

00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:12.768
Don't you think you're
getting a little too old

00:18:12.792 --> 00:18:15.226
for this rebel streak of yours?

00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:21.281
That's rich coming from you.

00:18:25.321 --> 00:18:30.302
Whatever you may think, my
choices have cost me dearly.

00:18:30.326 --> 00:18:35.140
Yeah. You're really hurting.

00:18:35.164 --> 00:18:38.210
My mother lives just
10 miles away from me.

00:18:38.234 --> 00:18:41.580
I haven't seen or spoken
to her in over 20 years.

00:18:41.604 --> 00:18:45.650
My father, when I run into him,
won't even fucking look at me.

00:18:45.674 --> 00:18:49.454
My sister, your mother,
denies I even exist.

00:18:49.478 --> 00:18:52.557
Yeah, well, that's why
they call it being shunned.

00:18:52.581 --> 00:18:54.862
[SPEAKS IN PENNSYLVANIA DUTCH]

00:18:56.202 --> 00:18:58.247
[SIGHS]

00:18:58.271 --> 00:19:00.538
[SPEAKS IN PENNSYLVANIA DUTCH]

00:19:02.425 --> 00:19:05.520
You can't begin to
understand how alone I am.

00:19:05.544 --> 00:19:08.106
I've lost count of
the people I hurt,

00:19:08.130 --> 00:19:11.632
and still I hurt
people every day.

00:19:13.603 --> 00:19:17.004
You have no idea what
that does to you inside.

00:19:19.541 --> 00:19:21.352
It's like a blade in your belly

00:19:21.376 --> 00:19:25.791
that has gradually
scraped you raw.

00:19:25.815 --> 00:19:28.426
I'm not buying it, uncle.

00:19:28.450 --> 00:19:32.197
You have everything
you've ever wanted.

00:19:32.221 --> 00:19:34.855
You're free.

00:19:37.693 --> 00:19:40.878
Why don't you just admit
that you like being bad?

00:19:47.653 --> 00:19:49.181
Do you realize

00:19:49.205 --> 00:19:53.552
no one else can
talk to me like that?

00:19:53.576 --> 00:19:56.488
You're the only person
who isn't scared of me.

00:19:56.512 --> 00:19:58.746
The only one.

00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:17.759
I'll drive you home.

00:20:17.783 --> 00:20:20.400
[ENGINE STARTS]

00:20:25.741 --> 00:20:27.418
[CROWD CHEERING]

00:20:27.442 --> 00:20:29.688
MAN 1: I want to welcome
our Camp Genoa Marines

00:20:29.712 --> 00:20:33.492
to view a private sparring
session with the champ.

00:20:33.516 --> 00:20:36.328
MAN 2: Ladies and gentlemen,
let me introduce a man

00:20:36.352 --> 00:20:38.213
who needs no introduction.

00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:40.916
Two-time cruiserweight
champion of the world,

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:43.368
honorary referee for
this weekend's fight,

00:20:43.392 --> 00:20:46.922
Banshee's own Sugar Bates!

00:20:46.946 --> 00:20:49.396
[CROWD CHEERING]

00:20:52.151 --> 00:20:55.364
Now, a special
gift for Mr. Sanchez

00:20:55.388 --> 00:20:58.350
from our sponsors at
Stark-Himmel Timepieces:

00:20:58.374 --> 00:21:02.037
a solid gold watch with a
one-of-a-kind diamond bezel

00:21:02.061 --> 00:21:04.206
designed especially
for the champ.

00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:07.092
This is yours. Wear it well.

00:21:07.116 --> 00:21:09.294
Got my invitation for the
cocktail party tomorrow

00:21:09.318 --> 00:21:10.895
and the fight on Saturday?

00:21:10.919 --> 00:21:12.263
LUCAS: I did.

00:21:12.287 --> 00:21:14.316
Thank you, gentlemen.

00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:17.569
Hey, listen, man, I wanna give
a<i> semper fi</i> to all my jarheads

00:21:17.593 --> 00:21:20.471
from Banshee's Camp
Genoa. ALL: Ooh-rah!

00:21:20.495 --> 00:21:23.258
Seems like you're
always hosting something.

00:21:23.282 --> 00:21:27.046
All right. Y'all ready to
see me whip some ass?

00:21:27.070 --> 00:21:29.080
ALL: Yeah!

00:21:29.104 --> 00:21:30.933
You just came in
to see him train?

00:21:30.957 --> 00:21:33.636
No. Actually, I came to see you.

00:21:33.660 --> 00:21:35.421
[GRUNTING]

00:21:35.445 --> 00:21:38.279
You heard about the
Schumacher boy OD'ing, right?

00:21:39.815 --> 00:21:43.261
Yeah, I did. It's terrible.

00:21:43.285 --> 00:21:45.914
[CROWD SHOUTING]

00:21:45.938 --> 00:21:48.083
Proctor, you told
me you had a talent

00:21:48.107 --> 00:21:50.458
for resolving problems
here in Banshee.

00:21:52.879 --> 00:21:56.308
I was kind of hoping you
could help me with this one.

00:21:56.332 --> 00:22:00.445
I found these in the
dead boy's pocket.

00:22:00.469 --> 00:22:03.198
The kids call them "skulls."

00:22:03.222 --> 00:22:05.683
You ever seen
pills like that before?

00:22:05.707 --> 00:22:08.186
Are you asking
me or accusing me?

00:22:08.210 --> 00:22:12.107
Heh. Why, I'm asking you, Kai.

00:22:12.131 --> 00:22:13.808
Just don't play
games with me, sheriff.

00:22:13.832 --> 00:22:15.594
I'm well aware of
Mayor Kendall's agenda.

00:22:15.618 --> 00:22:17.262
This has nothing
to do with Kendall.

00:22:17.286 --> 00:22:19.782
The boy means
well, but he's an idiot.

00:22:19.806 --> 00:22:22.167
On that at least I'm
sure we can agree.

00:22:22.191 --> 00:22:24.458
So if you'll excuse me...

00:22:26.245 --> 00:22:28.765
I'm busy trying to bring
good things to Banshee.

00:22:30.566 --> 00:22:32.233
Thanks for your time.

00:22:34.587 --> 00:22:36.203
ALL: Oh!

00:22:41.694 --> 00:22:43.094
[GRUNTING]

00:22:45.181 --> 00:22:47.025
[CROWD CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

